OL,7,F"He is trying to put a gentle gloss on
OL,8,Fsomething very sinister indeed."
OL,10,FMr McKone said Callaghan had targeted
OL,11,Fboys with "serious vulnerabilities"
OL,12,Fand that both were "still struggling
OL,13,Fnow" with what he did.
OL,15,FHe told jurors Callaghan "sought to
OL,16,Fjustify contact with (the first
OL,17,Fcomplainant) on the basis of trying to
OL,18,Fmake a troubled boy feel better about
OL,19,Fhimself" but that he was "thinking
OL,20,Fonly about himself and his own sexual
OL,21,Furges".
